77
00:09:31,606 --> 00:09:33,846
This one's as gentle
as a pussycat, Doc.

78
00:09:34,067 --> 00:09:36,467
Come in.
Have a seat.

79
00:09:36,695 --> 00:09:40,615
"Have a seat."
Curious expression.

80
00:09:42,662 --> 00:09:45,022
Well, let me introduce
myself. I'm--

81
00:09:45,206 --> 00:09:47,646
Dr. Mark Powell,
Chief of Clinical Psychiatry...

82
00:09:47,874 --> 00:09:50,234
of the Manhattan
Psychiatric Institute.

83
00:09:50,461 --> 00:09:53,141
Good. You know
where you are.

84
00:09:54,716 --> 00:09:58,556
Well, now, uh...
Prot, is it?

85
00:09:58,802 --> 00:10:01,962
"Prote."
I see, "Prote."

86
00:10:02,181 --> 00:10:05,021
Well, Prot,
we're here to--
May I?

87
00:10:06,521 --> 00:10:08,521
Please.

88
00:10:11,275 --> 00:10:14,155
Red delicious.
You call this variety.

89
00:10:15,406 --> 00:10:17,726
It's my favorite.

90
00:10:17,908 --> 00:10:21,068
I'd like to begin
by asking you...

91
00:10:21,328 --> 00:10:23,728
if you know
why you're here.

92
00:10:23,958 --> 00:10:27,078
Of course.
You think I'm crazy.

93
00:10:29,420 --> 00:10:33,780
We prefer the term "ill.''
Do you think you are ill?

94
00:10:34,092 --> 00:10:36,252
A little homesick, perhaps.

95
00:10:36,471 --> 00:10:38,951
Really.
Where is home?

96
00:10:39,180 --> 00:10:41,220
K-PAX.

97
00:10:41,434 --> 00:10:43,274
K-PAX?

98
00:10:43,436 --> 00:10:45,636
Capital "K,'' hyphen,
capitals "P-A-X.''

99
00:10:45,855 --> 00:10:48,135
K-PAX is a planet.

100
00:10:48,357 --> 00:10:51,677
But don't worry,
I'm not going to
leap out of your chest.

101
00:10:51,946 --> 00:10:54,706
I'm not worried.

102
00:10:54,909 --> 00:10:57,229
It’s just that I'm only
familiar with nine planets.

103
00:10:57,410 --> 00:10:59,690
Well, actually, there are ten,
but that doesn't matter.

104
00:10:59,870 --> 00:11:01,910
I'm not from
Your solar system.

105
00:11:02,082 --> 00:11:05,242
K-PAX is about 1 ,000
of your light-years
away from here...

106
00:11:05,504 --> 00:11:08,104
in what you would call
Your constellation Lyra.

107
00:11:08,337 --> 00:11:10,457
That's quite a ways.

108
00:11:10,674 --> 00:11:12,594
I'm curious.
How did you get to Earth?

109
00:11:15,597 --> 00:11:18,877
It's a matter of harnessing
the energy of light.

110
00:11:19,099 --> 00:11:21,539
I know that sounds
crazy to you.

111
00:11:21,728 --> 00:11:24,688
You beings are eons away
from discovering light travel.

112
00:11:26,777 --> 00:11:28,697
You travel
at the speed of light?

113
00:11:28,903 --> 00:11:33,823
Oh, no. We can travel
many times that speed.
Various multiples of "C.''

114
00:11:34,118 --> 00:11:38,118
Otherwise, the trip here
would have taken about
1 ,000 years now, wouldn't it?

115
00:11:41,251 --> 00:11:43,851
What if, um,
I were to tell you...

116
00:11:44,087 --> 00:11:46,807
that according to a man
who lived on our planet
named Einstein,

117
00:11:47,007 --> 00:11:51,727
that nothing can travel
faster than the speed
of light?

118
00:11:52,054 --> 00:11:55,134
I would say that you misread
Einstein, Dr. Powell.
May I call you Mark?

119
00:11:55,349 --> 00:11:58,309
You see, Mark,
what Einstein actually said...

120
00:11:58,559 --> 00:12:00,719
was that nothing can accelerate
to the speed of light,

121
00:12:00,939 --> 00:12:02,819
because its mass
would become infinite.

122
00:12:03,024 --> 00:12:06,864
Einstein said nothing about
entities already traveling
at the speed of light or faster,

123
00:12:07,113 --> 00:12:10,193
- at tachyon speeds.
- Tachyon?

124
00:12:10,449 --> 00:12:13,929
I detect a note
of skepticism, Dr. Powell.

125
00:12:14,204 --> 00:12:16,524
Oh, not at all.
It's just that you--

126
00:12:16,708 --> 00:12:18,828
You speak English
so well.

127
00:12:18,999 --> 00:12:21,879
I'm amazed.
Well, English isn't that
difficult a language to learn.

128
00:12:22,127 --> 00:12:27,727
You should try speaking--

129
00:12:31,138 --> 00:12:33,978
I'm--
I'm confused.

130
00:12:34,184 --> 00:12:36,624
Maybe you can explain
it to me. Uh...

131
00:12:36,813 --> 00:12:39,773
how is it that
being a visitor from space,

132
00:12:39,981 --> 00:12:42,421
that you-you look
so much like me...

133
00:12:42,652 --> 00:12:45,012
or anyone else from Earth?

134
